qas.question: What is the highest court in Brazil?
What are the two areas this court has supremacy over?

answers.text: cases that may be unconstitutional or final habeas corpus pleads for criminal cases

qas.question: Which legislative bodies does this court sit in cases over?

answers.text: cases involving members of congress, senators

qas.question: What other government officials are subject to judgments of Brazil's highest court?

answers.text: ministers of state, members of the high courts and the President and Vice-President of the Republic

qas.question: What is Brazil's high court for labor law?

answers.text: The Superior Labour Tribunal (Tribunal Superior do Trabalho)

qas.question: The Superior Labour Tribunal oversees what type of elections?

plausible_answers.text: cases that may be unconstitutional or final habeas corpus pleads for criminal cases

qas.question: What two types of cases does the Superior Military Tribunal only review?
What conflicting outcomes does the Superior Electoral Tribunal deal with?
What is the Brazilian name for the Supreme Court?

context: In Brazil, the <a0_0>Supreme Federal Tribunal (<b8_0>Supremo Tribunal Federal<b8_0/>)<a0_0/> is the highest court. It is both the constitutional court and the court of last resort in Brazilian law. It only reviews <a1_0><b6_0>cases that may be unconstitutional or final habeas corpus pleads for criminal cases<b6_0/><a1_0/>. It also judges, in original jurisdiction, <a2_0>cases involving members of congress, senators<a2_0/>, <a3_0>ministers of state, members of the high courts and the President and Vice-President of the Republic<a3_0/>. The Superior Court of Justice (Tribunal Superior de Justiça) reviews State and Federal Circuit courts decisions for civil law and criminal law cases, when dealing with federal law or conflicting <b7_0>rulings<b7_0/>. <a4_0>The Superior Labour Tribunal (Tribunal Superior do Trabalho)<a4_0/> reviews cases involving labour law. The Superior Electoral Tribunal (Tribunal Superior Eleitoral) is the court of last resort of electoral law, and also oversees <b5_0>general elections<b5_0/>. The Superior Military Tribunal (Tribunal Superior Militar) is the highest court in matters of federal military law.
